Residents of Journalists’ Estate and adjourning communities in Arepo, a highbrow town, in Owode Local Council of Ogun State are elated over Governor Dapo Abiodun’s recent intervention on the 2.5km road.  “The simple law of value analysis shows that by implication, the value of landed properties in and  Arepo axis would shore up after the completion of the all-important community feeder road. The governor has walked his talk when he promised residents a face-lift in infrastructural development in the area.      
    
Another resident, Soji Kamoru, said he was elated that the governor had lived up to his promise. According to him, he is eagerly waiting for its commissioning to open up the estate more.
   
He said: “With the quality of work done so far, I have forgotten the initial pains we all experienced during the construction. I just pray that they complete the last segments.” 